= Power Systems Protection
- Consists of 3 main elements
 - Instrument transformers, relays, circuit breakers
  - Distance relays - triggers when voltage to current ratio is below a set impedance value
- Dependable - operates correctly for all faults
- Secure - doeos not operate for non-faulted conditions
== Protection zones
- Protected elements enclosed in zones
- Transducers and circuit breaker locations determine zones
- *zones should overlap* to avoid unprotected elements
- Must open line on both ends of fault
- 
== Symetrical fault
- All 3 phases faulted at once
 - e.g. 3 phases shorted to ground
== Non-symmetrical faults
- single line fault
- line-to-line faults
- line-to-line-to-ground faults
